xt\":\"**Considering metadata generation**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how Forge generates metadata externally and that we shouldn't edit the configs ourselves. It seems like tests run under native by default, so direct v3 should work if the metadata contains our test stubs. I'm curious about the reflection process from the library to test classes in native mode. Also, the agent creates metadata for javax.jmdns.JmDNS and ServiceInfo, but I wonder if user-code-filter might be excluding javax. Let's take a closer look!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_hIIuXxMIaIILzqRqgG1Y2wEz|fc_026dd3de8ca7d1aa0169fb9437a8ec819d93e5600763caad13", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/ch.qos.reload4j/reload4j/1.2.19/user-code-filter.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 886, "output": 632, "cacheRead": 16896, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 18414, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778095147648, "responseId": "resp_026dd3de8ca7d1aa0169fb942ca8a4819d8834bf603e60aef5"}}
